casebody.data:
In the INTEREST OF D.C.A. Juvenile Officer, Respondent,
v.
D.C.A., Appellant. WD 81557 Missouri Court of Appeals, Western District. ORDER FILED: March 26, 2019 Mary Barnard, Fulton, Missouri, Attorney for Respondent. Craig A. Johnston, Assistant State Public Defender, Columbia, MO, Attorney for Appellant. Before Division Three: Mark D. Pfeiffer, Presiding Judge, and Lisa White Hardwick and Anthony Rex Gabbert, Judges

Order

Per Curiam:

By and through counsel, D.C.A. appeals from the order of adjudication of the Circuit Court of Callaway County, Missouri, Family Court Division, finding that the Juvenile Officer proved beyond a reasonable doubt that D.C.A. committed acts that would constitute felonies if committed by an adult. Because a published opinion would have no precedential value, a memorandum of law has been provided to the parties. The adjudication order is affirmed. Rule 84.16(b).
